# Setting Up on Windows for Jenkins

# Prerequisites
# Minimum hardware requirements : 256 MB of RAM 1 GB of drive space 

# Software requirements:
Java 21 or later: see the Java Requirements page
Web browser: see the Web Browser Compatibility page

Setting Up Java, Git, Maven on Windows for Jenkins

install and configure Java (JDK), Git, Maven, and Jenkins on a Windows machine.

Install & Configure Git

Git is a version control tool and is widely used with Jenkins.

Download Git for Windows from https://git-scm.com/downloads/win.

For windows Git for Windows/x64 Portable. (as per your windows machine).

Install it.

after installation - Git Bash

Configure your details :

git config --global user.name "your_name"
git config --global user.email "your_email"
git config --global --list
git --version

Install & Configure Java (JDK)

Jenkins and Maven require Java to run, so let’s begin here.

Download JDK (Windows .exe installer).

https://download.oracle.com/java/21/latest/jdk-21_windows-x64_bin.exe.

Install it (default path: C:\Program Files\Java\jdk-XX).

Configure environment variables :
Add JAVA_HOME → C:\Program Files\Java\jdk-XX
Add bin path to PATH.

Configure your details :

echo %JAVA_HOME%
java --version

Note: Jenkins currently supports JDK 17 and 21. Avoid using JDK 24.

Install & Configure Maven

Maven is a build automation tool often integrated with Jenkins.

Download Maven from apache.org.

https://dlcdn.apache.org/maven/mvnd/1.0.2/maven-mvnd-1.0.2-windows-amd64.zip

Extract it to a directory.

Set environment variables :
MAVEN_HOME = C:\apache-maven
Add %MAVEN_HOME%\bin to PATH.

Configure your details :

mvn -version

Reboot system

Install & Configure Jenkins

Jenkins is the backbone of DevOps automation.

Download Jenkins Windows installer (.msi) from jenkins.io.

https://2.mirrors.in.sahilister.net/jenkins/windows-stable/2.516.2/jenkins.msi

Install → it auto-detects Java.

Open Jenkins in your browser :

http://localhost:8080

Create an admin user → install suggested plugins → dashboard will appear.

To avoid issues, follow this installation sequence :

Git

Java (JDK 17)

Maven

Reboot System

Jenkins
